  "text": "Adipose tissue inflammation, with accumulation of immune cells, is believed to play a causal role in insulin resistance, [CITATION_1] and TLR4 expression on hematopoietic cells promotes this effect. [CITATION_2] Male DDC-fed LDLR Ϫ/Ϫ mice develop insulin resistance, obesity, systemic inflammation, and macrophage infiltration into epididymal adipose tissue. [CITATION_3] We therefore investigated whether S100A9 deficiency would affect these parameters.",
